# PR Visual Evidence (mandatory)

Part of the full **`pr-merge-ready-workflow.mdc`** handoff. Every **product/runtime PR** must include visual proof captured from the **local dev stack** (`http://localhost:8080`). This gate is **not skippable** when opening or updating a PR that touches user-visible behavior.

## Required artifacts

| Artifact | Minimum | Source |
|----------|---------|--------|
| Screenshots | 1+ labeled PNGs showing the changed UI/states | Playwright `e2e/pr-evidence/*.spec.ts` |
| Demo video | 1 H.264 MP4 of the flow | Playwright WebM converted via `ffmpeg` in capture script, uploaded to GitHub user-attachments |

Workflow-only PRs (`.cursor/**`, `AGENTS.md`, `scripts/mcp.template.json`) are exempt.

## Agent workflow (before `gh pr create`)

1. **Author or update** a focused spec under `e2e/pr-evidence/` when existing specs do not cover the change. Do **not** rely on `smoke-dashboard.spec.ts` when the PR changes specific UI.
2. **Capture** on the local stack:
   ```powershell
   .\scripts\pr-evidence\Invoke-PrEvidence.ps1 `
     -Flow "<short-slug>" `
     -Spec "e2e/pr-evidence/<feature>.spec.ts"
   ```
3. **Merge** `tmp/pr-evidence/<slug>/evidence-markdown.md` into the PR body under **Screenshots/Videos** (or paste the generated section verbatim).
4. **After** `gh pr create`, **publish** the evidence comment (hosted URLs for inline playback):
   ```powershell
   .\scripts\pr-evidence\Invoke-PrEvidence.ps1 `
     -Flow "<short-slug>" `
     -Spec "e2e/pr-evidence/<feature>.spec.ts" `
     -PrNumber <num> `
     -Publish
   ```

If capture fails, **stop before opening the PR** — fix the spec or stack; do not open a PR without evidence.

## When to add new Playwright specs

- New route, form, dialog, integration UI, or UX change: **add** `e2e/pr-evidence/<feature>.spec.ts`.
- Use `evidenceScreenshot()` from `e2e/pr-evidence/shared/evidence-helpers.ts` at each meaningful state.
- Reuse `equipqr-test` fixtures (`gotoDashboard`, personas) for deterministic seeded data.

## Touched user-visible behavior standard

When a PR touches **any user-visible behavior** — including indirect changes to an existing feature, contextual help links, or equipqr.info documentation tied to app surfaces — evidence must prove the **real workflow still works end-to-end** from discovery through completion, not just that a page renders.

Minimum bar for feature-adjacent changes:

1. **Functional proof** — exercise the changed path on the local stack (`http://localhost:8080`) the way a user would (submit forms, navigate between surfaces, export when applicable).
2. **Discovery proof** — when docs or in-app Help links change, capture evidence that a user can reach the relevant guide from each surfaced entry point (admin console, equipment details, QR dialog, public form, Help Center nav) and that the guide shows the expected scenario content.
3. **Regression check** — rerun the existing feature evidence spec when the underlying feature already has one; do not replace deep functional proof with link-only screenshots.

Shallow smoke (empty state only, invalid token only, or static page load without completing the workflow) is **not** sufficient when the PR changes how users discover or use that behavior.

## Storage and display

- **Screenshots:** preview Supabase public bucket `landing-page-images` under `pr-evidence/{branch}/` via `scripts/upload-screenshot.ts` with `OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN`.
- **Demo video:** GitHub user-attachments via `scripts/upload-github-asset.ts` with **`GH_SESSION_TOKEN`** (browser `user_session` cookie — not a PAT). See `scripts/pr-evidence/README.md` for one-time setup (`gh image extract-token`).
- GitHub renders the demo as an **inline video player** when the markdown is a bare `https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/...` URL on its own line. Screenshots still use `![alt](https://...supabase.co/...)`.

## Handoff requirements

PR handoff must cite:

- Capture command run (copy-pasteable).
- Spec file path.
- Confirmation that screenshots **and** demo MP4 were uploaded (or PR comment URL after `-Publish`).

## Relationship to local verify

This rule complements `local-verify-before-preview-push.mdc`. Local E2E proves correctness; PR visual evidence proves **what changed** for reviewers at a glance.
